				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The new task system.<a name="64651"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 28 04 1:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I started fresh into EQ after OOW kicked in.  My wife and i have tried several of these tasks and soloing doesnt seem to be an option.  We have done tasks from the first two sets of task givers (1-30 range).
<br />

<br />
I really dont think SoE intended any of this stuff to be soloable.  With the way they are pushing groups (LD Exp, Making soloing harder 65+, ect.) i really think these are all meant to be done in a full group.  Sad part is, i dont know if a full group of 10-12's could pull off the tasks that my wife has been given.  Nearly everyone of them i have had to bail her out with my 28bard after she has died several times.
<br />

<br />
Even after saying this, i dont think the task system is a bad one.  You gain Faction, learn the area around your starting city, and gain a small amount of exp and pp.  For a total newbie like my wife it is VERY good with the exception that they are so difficult.  She has tried to solo each one of them as a mage and has only succeeded(sp) once (out of 9 or 10).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
